full_text: UserAccess can be configured to allow external users to be assigned to groups and producer codes from other organizations. For training purpose, the configuration parameter ExternalUserAccess it is set to ProtectInternal, which allows external users to be assigned to groups and producer codes in any external organizations, but not the internal organization. After logging in a superuser, find an external user. For example, Peyton Armstrong. Select the user. Click Edit. Go to the Access tab. Because the external user access level is set to ProtectInternal, you can add groups by searching within other external organizations. Click Search and select a group. Click the Organization Search icon. Find the Organization for Builders Risk Brokers. Click Search. Click Search. Select the External Organization Builders Risk Brokers. Click Search again on the Search Groups page. Select the Producer's group. Users inherit producer codes from their assigned groups. Try to add groups within an internal organization. Click Search and select a group. Click the Organization Search icon. Find the internal organization, Enigma Fire and Casualty. Click Search. Select the Internal Organization. On the Search Groups page. Click Search again. On the Search Groups page, make sure to click Search again. Select a group from the internal organization. An error message is displayed, stating that the user does not have access to the group. Note that it can be configured to assign the external user to groups in the internal organization. You can add additional producer codes by clicking Add. Select the external organization. First, find the external organization, All Risk Insurance. Enter the name. Click Search. Select the external organization. On the Producer Codes page, click Search again. Select the Producer Code. Click Update to save the changes. You can also add users to a group by going to the group. Go to the Users tab. Click Edit. Add a user from an external organization, Commercial Insurers. Click the Search icon for Organization. Enter the name. Click Search. Select the Organization. Enter the name.   On the Search Users page, click Search again. Select the user to be added. Save the changes. This is the end of demonstration for External User Access. segments.text: UserAccess can be configured to allow external users to be assigned to groups and producer codes from other organizations. For training purpose, the configuration parameter ExternalUserAccess it is set to ProtectInternal, which allows external users to be assigned to groups and producer codes in any external organizations, but not the internal organization. After logging in a superuser, find an external user. For example, Peyton Armstrong. Select the user.
Click Edit. Go to the Access tab.

Because the external user access level is set to ProtectInternal, you can add groups by searching within other external organizations. Click Search and select a group. Click the Organization Search icon. Find the Organization for Builders Risk Brokers.
Click Search. Click Search. Select the External Organization Builders Risk Brokers. Click Search again on the Search Groups page. Select the Producer's group.

Users inherit producer codes from their assigned groups. Try to add groups within an internal organization. Click Search and select a group. Click the Organization Search icon. Find the internal organization, Enigma Fire and Casualty. Click Search. Select the Internal Organization.
On the Search Groups page. Click Search again.
On the Search Groups page, make sure to click Search again. Select a group from the internal organization.
An error message is displayed, stating that the user does not have access to the group.
Note that it can be configured to assign the external user to groups in the internal organization.
You can add additional producer codes by clicking Add.
Select the external organization.
First, find the external organization, All Risk Insurance. Enter the name. Click Search.
Select the external organization. On the Producer Codes page, click Search again. Select the Producer Code.
Click Update to save the changes.
You can also add users to a group by going to the group.
Go to the Users tab.
Click Edit.
Add a user from an external organization, Commercial Insurers.
Click the Search icon for Organization.
Enter the name.
Click Search.
Select the Organization.
Enter the name.
On the Search Users page, click Search again.
Select the user to be added.
Save the changes.
This is the end of demonstration for External User Access.
